        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-spotlights-h1-1-dutch-government-fell?source=website" target="_blank">Dutch government fell</a> when Geert Wildersâ€™ far-right Party for Freedom (PVV) left the ruling coalition over immigration policy. Wilders accused his coalition partners of rejecting his strict 10-point <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-spotlights-h1-2-asylum-proposal?source=website" target="_blank">asylum proposal</a>. This plan aimed to halt all asylum applications and suspend family reunification for refugees.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
